        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 8 at 6:14PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 614 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Darby, or 7 miles southeast of Deep Gap, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
North Wilkesboro...
Wilkesboro...
Boomer...
Wilbar...
Mc Grady...
Darby...
and Windy Gap.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until midnight EDT for
northwestern North Carolina...and southwestern Virginia.</instruction>
